Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: The Huntington
Description: Encompasses about 130 acres of 16 distinct themed botanical gardens, a mauseleum, conservatory, library, and art museum.

Name: Sandos Playacar
Description: An amazing resort in Playa del Carmen, Mexico with endless things to do. Soak up the sun on the beach, explore the local cenotes and Mayan ruins, and more. It is situated south of Cancun.

Name: San Juan Cosala
Description: You can enjoy heated pools, jacuzzis, water slides, and more thanks to the thermal water taken from the hot springs of Chapala. This hotel/ water park is located in Jocotepec, Mexico.

Name: Zacoalco de Torres
Description: Zocoalco de Torres is my mother's hometown located in Jalisco, Mexico. I consider this place to be my 2nd home as I have many family members living there. Fun fact: The region primarily produces equipal-style wood and pigskin furniture.

Name: Santa Anita Creek
Description: Santa Anita Creeks is a 10.4 mile long stream in LA county. I usually hike along the beautiful trails near Monrovia, CA. One of the trails even leads to a waterfall, where people can jump and frolick about.
